---
import CTA from '@/components/CTA.astro';
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '@/lib/seo';
import { firm } from '@/lib/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Matthew G. Steel is the founder of Steel & Associates, A Professional Law Corporation, based in Gretna, Louisiana and built around disciplined record work."
  path="/about/"
  schemas={[breadcrumbSchema([{ href: '/', label: 'Home' }, { href: '/about/', label: 'About' }])]}
>
  <section class="page-hero container">
    <div class="page-hero__content">
      <p class="hero-kicker">Attorney and firm story</p>
      <h1>{firm.attorney}</h1>
      <p class="page-subhead">
        Immigration lawyer and founder of {firm.name}, based in Gretna, Louisiana and built around
        language, culture, family, systems, and careful record work.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="page-summary-card" data-nosnippet>
      <h2>Practice focus</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Family immigration and humanitarian relief</li>
        <li>Removal defense and urgent record review</li>
        <li>Employment immigration and business-facing workflows</li>
        <li>Consumer-facing credit, traffic, and notary intake lanes</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="content-grid container">
    <div class="content-flow">
      <article class="content-block">
        <h2>Local roots, federal reach</h2>
        <p>
          The firm is rooted in the New Orleans and Westbank area, but immigration work often
          reaches far past one city line. The office is built to move between local relationships,
          multilingual intake, and federal systems without turning the client into a data dump.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="content-block">
        <h2>Record-first by design</h2>
        <p>
          The point is not performance. The point is a record that can survive a review, a filing,
          a deadline, an audit, a court date, or a follow-up without collapsing under loose facts.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="content-block">
        <h2>Private systems behind public work</h2>
        <p>
          The public website is only the front room. Behind it is a more disciplined operating stack
          for communication, storage, scheduling, credentials, drafting, and internal review.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <aside class="sidebar-panel" data-nosnippet>
      <h2>Visit the office</h2>
      <p>{firm.addressLines[0]}</p>
      <p>{firm.addressLines[1]}</p>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href="/contact/">Schedule a Consultation</a>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <CTA
    title="Need the next move, not a speech?"
    copy="Use the secure contact form when the matter needs review, a deadline triage, or a clear route into the office."
  />
</BaseLayout>
